text:
When attempting to target a lambda that is called on an S3 CreateBucket - the call does not find a match due to a missing field in the C/W event construct. There are no additional fields available in the API to trigger the creation of the required event field. This is critical as the example code provided depends on this functionality - out of the box, the example fails.

Here's the event that CloudCustodian creates - which is missing the source portion of the event JSON.

```
{
  "detail-type": [
    "AWS API Call via CloudTrail"
  ],
  "detail": {
    "eventSource": [
      "s3.amazonaws.com"
    ],
    "eventName": [
      "CreateBucket"
    ]
  }
}
```

Here's a functioning event's JSON that was manually created that correctly triggers the lambda function

```
{
  "source": [
    "aws.s3"
  ],
  "detail-type": [
    "AWS API Call via CloudTrail"
  ],
  "detail": {
    "eventSource": [
      "s3.amazonaws.com"
    ],
    "eventName": [
      "CreateBucket"
    ]
  }
}
```
